PLACEHOLDER_FAQ_TITLE: Frequently Asked Questions about Our Ethereum Transaction Analysis App
ACCORDION_ANSWER_1: Our app provides real-time monitoring and analysis of new transactions on the Ethereum blockchain. It helps you stay up-to-date with the latest activity and identify potential issues or opportunities.
ACCORDION_ANSWER_2: We connect directly to Ethereum nodes to stream incoming transaction data. Advanced algorithms then analyze this data, flagging notable transactions based on customizable rules and heuristics.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_3: What kind of transactions are detected?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_3: The app can detect a wide variety of transaction types including large value transfers, interactions with popular DeFi protocols, deployment of new smart contracts, and more.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_4: Can I customize what gets flagged?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_4: Yes, you can fully configure the detection rules to suit your specific needs and interests. Filter by transaction value, contract addresses, function signatures, and many other parameters.
FAQ_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Get answers to common questions about our Ethereum transaction analysis app
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_1: Our app provides real-time analysis of new transactions on the Ethereum blockchain. It monitors the network, decodes incoming transactions, and surfaces insights and analytics.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_2: What kind of analysis is provided?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_2: The app analyzes transaction data like sender, recipient, value transferred, gas fees paid, and any encoded data or smart contract interactions. It flags anomalies, correlates related transactions, and visualizes patterns.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_3: How quickly are new transactions analyzed?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_3: Our infrastructure can analyze new transactions within seconds of them being included in a new Ethereum block. The analytics stream updates with negligible delay.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_4: Can I integrate the app with my own systems?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: Yes, we provide APIs and webhooks that allow you to pipe the real-time transaction analysis data into your own databases, dashboards, alerts and workflows.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_5: We have a free starter plan for low volumes, and scalable paid plans for higher transaction throughput. Enterprise plans with SLAs and premium support are also available.
